{{Wireless embedded system |brand=Actiontec |model=802AA |revision= |est_release_date= |fcc_date=12/21/2001 |manuf_country=Taiwan |is_manuf=No |manuf=Orient Semiconductor Electronics |availability= |type=access point |fcc_id=LNQ802AA |pwr_v=3.3 |pwr_amp=3.5 |pwr_conn=barrel |cpu1_brand=Motorola |cpu1_model=MPC8245;M, XPC8245LZU266A, 1K78P, CRBJ0137, HKG; |cpu1_cspeed=266 |fla1=8 |fla1_brand=Intel |fla1_model=E28F640J3A-120 |ram1=16 |ram1_brand=Micron |ram1_model=MT48LC2M32B2 |ram1_num=2 |expansion_if_types= |expansion_usb_num= |jtag= |serial=yes,, DE-9,, |wi1_chip1_brand=Atheros |wi1_chip1_model=AR5210A |wi1_chip2_brand=Atheros |wi1_chip2_model=AR5110 |wi1_802dot11_protocols=a |wi1_ant_conn=MMCX |eth_none= |eth_cpu= |eth_chip1_brand=National Semiconductor |eth_chip1_model=DP83815 |lan_speed=100M |lan_ports=1 |wan_ports= |flags= |tp_firmware= |802dot11_protocols=a |default_ssid=ACTIONTEC_11A |default_ssid_regex=^ACTIONTEC_11A$ |default_ip=192.168.0.250 |default_user=Admin |default_pass= |oui= |oui_eth= }} {{TagLine|802.11a Wireless Access Point}} :[http://www.actiontec.com/support/product_details.php?pid=174 Support page]
"ACTIONTEC", "802AA REV.1A" and "0145"is silkscreened on the board :in the [https://fccid.io/LNQ802AA/Internal-Photos/Internal-Photos-189424 FCC photos] (see also [[Actiontec]]).
The FCC label indicates some involvement of ''Orient Semiconductor Electronics'' :(A partner you can count on). They are presumed to be the manufacturer.
This device uses the [[Atheros AR5BAP-00030]] (AP30) reference design. :The sample SSID in the manual is specified as ''ACTIONTEC_11A''. This is assumed to be the correct, but there is pretty much no ''WiGLE'' :support for this device.
